Enums.Name: VisualFeaturesImpl

AllowedValues.Name: tags
AllowedValues.Description: Extract content tags for thousands of recognizable objects, living beings, scenery, and actions that appear in the image.

AllowedValues.Name: caption
AllowedValues.Description: Generate a human-readable caption sentence that describes the content of the image.

AllowedValues.Name: denseCaptions
AllowedValues.Description: Generate human-readable caption sentences for up to 10 different regions in the image, including one for the whole image.

AllowedValues.Name: objects
AllowedValues.Description: Object detection. This is similar to tags, but focused on detecting physical objects in the image and returning their location.

AllowedValues.Name: read
AllowedValues.Description: Extract printed or handwritten text from the image. Also known as Optical Character Recognition (OCR).

AllowedValues.Name: smartCrops
AllowedValues.Description: Find representative sub-regions of the image for thumbnail generation, at desired aspect ratios, with priority given to detected faces.

AllowedValues.Name: people
AllowedValues.Description: Detect people in the image and return their location.

Enums.Description: The visual features supported by the Image Analysis service

Models.Name: ImageAnalysisResult
Models.Description: Represents the outcome of an Image Analysis operation.

Properties.Name: caption
Properties.Description: The generated phrase that describes the content of the analyzed image.

Type.Name: CaptionResult
Type.Description: Represents a generated phrase that describes the content of the whole image.

Properties.Name: confidence
Properties.Description:
A score, in the range of 0 to 1 (inclusive), representing the confidence that this description is accurate.
Higher values indicating higher confidence.

Properties.Name: text
Properties.Description: The text of the caption.

Properties.Name: denseCaptions
Properties.Description:
The up to 10 generated phrases, the first describing the content of the whole image,
and the others describing the content of different regions of the image.

Type.Name: DenseCaptionsResult
Type.Description:
Represents a list of up to 10 image captions for different regions of the image.
The first caption always applies to the whole image.

Properties.Name: values
Properties.Description: The list of image captions.

ElementType.Name: DenseCaption
ElementType.Description: Represents a generated phrase that describes the content of the whole image or a region in the image

Properties.Name: confidence
Properties.Description:
A score, in the range of 0 to 1 (inclusive), representing the confidence that this description is accurate.
Higher values indicating higher confidence.

Properties.Name: text
Properties.Description: The text of the caption.

Properties.Name: boundingBox
Properties.Description: The image region of which this caption applies.

Type.Name: ImageBoundingBox
Type.Description: A basic rectangle specifying a sub-region of the image.

Properties.Name: x
Properties.Description: X-coordinate of the top left point of the area, in pixels.

Properties.Name: y
Properties.Description: Y-coordinate of the top left point of the area, in pixels.

Properties.Name: width
Properties.Description: Width of the area, in pixels.

Properties.Name: height
Properties.Description: Height of the area, in pixels.

Properties.Name: metadata
Properties.Description: Metadata associated with the analyzed image.

Type.Name: ImageMetadata
Type.Description: Metadata associated with the analyzed image.

Properties.Name: height
Properties.Description: The height of the image in pixels.

Properties.Name: width
Properties.Description: The width of the image in pixels.

Properties.Name: modelVersion
Properties.Description: The cloud AI model used for the analysis

Properties.Name: objects
Properties.Description: A list of detected physical objects in the analyzed image, and their location.

Type.Name: ObjectsResult
Type.Description: Represents a list of physical object detected in an image and their location.

Properties.Name: values
Properties.Description: A list of physical object detected in an image and their location.

ElementType.Name: DetectedObject
ElementType.Description: Represents a physical object detected in an image.

Properties.Name: boundingBox
Properties.Description: A rectangular boundary where the object was detected.

Properties.Name: tags
Properties.Description: A single-item list containing the object information.

ElementType.Name: DetectedTag
ElementType.Description:
A content entity observation in the image. A tag can be a physical object, living being, scenery, or action
that appear in the image.

Properties.Name: confidence
Properties.Description:
A score, in the range of 0 to 1 (inclusive), representing the confidence that this entity was observed.
Higher values indicating higher confidence.

Properties.Name: name
Properties.Description: Name of the entity.

Properties.Name: people
Properties.Description: A list of detected people in the analyzed image, and their location.

Type.Name: PeopleResult
Type.Description: Represents a list of people detected in an image and their location.

Properties.Name: values
Properties.Description: A list of people detected in an image and their location.

ElementType.Name: DetectedPerson
ElementType.Description: Represents a person detected in an image.

Properties.Name: boundingBox
Properties.Description: A rectangular boundary where the person was detected.

Properties.Name: confidence
Properties.Description:
A score, in the range of 0 to 1 (inclusive), representing the confidence that this detection was accurate.
Higher values indicating higher confidence.

Properties.Name: read
Properties.Description: The extracted printed and hand-written text in the analyze image. Also knows as OCR.

Type.Name: ReadResult
Type.Description: The results of a Read (OCR) operation.

Properties.Name: blocks
Properties.Description: A list of text blocks in the image. At the moment only one block is returned, containing all the text detected in the image.

ElementType.Name: DetectedTextBlock
ElementType.Description: Represents a single block of detected text in the image.

Properties.Name: lines
Properties.Description: A list of text lines in this block.

ElementType.Name: DetectedTextLine
ElementType.Description: Represents a single line of text in the image.

Properties.Name: text
Properties.Description: Text content of the detected text line.

Properties.Name: boundingPolygon
Properties.Description: A bounding polygon around the text line. At the moment only quadrilaterals are supported (represented by 4 image points).

ElementType.Name: ImagePoint
ElementType.Description: Represents the coordinates of a single pixel in the image.

Properties.Name: x
Properties.Description: The horizontal x-coordinate of this point, in pixels. Zero values corresponds to the left-most pixels in the image.

Properties.Name: y
Properties.Description: The vertical y-coordinate of this point, in pixels. Zero values corresponds to the top-most pixels in the image.

Properties.Name: words
Properties.Description: A list of words in this line.

ElementType.Name: DetectedTextWord
ElementType.Description:
A word object consisting of a contiguous sequence of characters. For non-space delimited languages,
such as Chinese, Japanese, and Korean, each character is represented as its own word.

Properties.Name: text
Properties.Description: Text content of the word.

Properties.Name: boundingPolygon
Properties.Description: A bounding polygon around the word. At the moment only quadrilaterals are supported (represented by 4 image points).

Properties.Name: confidence
Properties.Description: The level of confidence that the word was detected. Confidence scores span the range of 0.0 to 1.0 (inclusive), with higher values indicating a higher confidence of detection.

Properties.Name: smartCrops
Properties.Description:
A list of crop regions at the desired as aspect ratios (if provided) that can be used as image thumbnails.
These regions preserve as much content as possible from the analyzed image, with priority given to detected faces.

Type.Name: SmartCropsResult
Type.Description:
Smart cropping result. A list of crop regions at the desired as aspect ratios (if provided) that can be used as image thumbnails.
These regions preserve as much content as possible from the analyzed image, with priority given to detected faces.

Properties.Name: values
Properties.Description: A list of crop regions.

ElementType.Name: CropRegion
ElementType.Description:
A region at the desired aspect ratio that can be used as image thumbnail.
The region preserves as much content as possible from the analyzed image, with priority given to detected faces.

Properties.Name: aspectRatio
Properties.Description:
The aspect ratio of the crop region.
Aspect ratio is calculated by dividing the width of the region in pixels by its height in pixels.
The aspect ratio will be in the range 0.75 to 1.8 (inclusive) if provided by the developer during the analyze call.
Otherwise, it will be in the range 0.5 to 2.0 (inclusive).

Properties.Name: boundingBox
Properties.Description: The bounding box of the region.

Properties.Name: tags
Properties.Description: A list of content tags in the analyzed image.

Type.Name: TagsResult
Type.Description:
A list of entities observed in the image. Tags can be physical objects, living being, scenery, or actions
that appear in the image.

Properties.Name: values
Properties.Description: A list of tags.

Models.Name: ImageUrl
Models.Description: An object holding the publicly reachable URL of an image to analyze.

Properties.Name: url
Properties.Description: Publicly reachable URL of an image to analyze.

Operations.Name: analyzeFromImageData
Operations.Description: Performs a single Image Analysis operation

Parameters.Name: endpoint
Parameters.Description:
Azure AI Computer Vision endpoint (protocol and hostname, for example:
https://<resource-name>.cognitiveservices.azure.com).

Parameters.Name: apiVersion
Parameters.Description: The API version to use for this operation.

Parameters.Name: contentType
Parameters.Description: The format of the HTTP payload.

Parameters.Name: visualFeatures
Parameters.Description:
A list of visual features to analyze.
Seven visual features are supported: Caption, DenseCaptions, Read (OCR), Tags, Objects, SmartCrops, and People.
At least one visual feature must be specified.

Parameters.Name: language
Parameters.Description:
The desired language for result generation (a two-letter language code).
If this option is not specified, the default value 'en' is used (English).
See https://aka.ms/cv-languages for a list of supported languages.

Parameters.Name: genderNeutralCaption
Parameters.Description:
Boolean flag for enabling gender-neutral captioning for Caption and Dense Captions features.
By default captions may contain gender terms (for example: 'man', 'woman', or 'boy', 'girl'). 
If you set this to "true", those will be replaced with gender-neutral terms (for example: 'person' or 'child').

Parameters.Name: smartCropsAspectRatios
Parameters.Description:
A list of aspect ratios to use for smart cropping.
Aspect ratios are calculated by dividing the target crop width in pixels by the height in pixels.
Supported values are between 0.75 and 1.8 (inclusive).
If this parameter is not specified, the service will return one crop region with an aspect
ratio it sees fit between 0.5 and 2.0 (inclusive).

Parameters.Name: modelVersion
Parameters.Description:
The version of cloud AI-model used for analysis.
The format is the following: 'latest' (default value) or 'YYYY-MM-DD' or 'YYYY-MM-DD-preview', where 'YYYY', 'MM', 'DD' are the year, month and day associated with the model.
This is not commonly set, as the default always gives the latest AI model with recent improvements.
If however you would like to make sure analysis results do not change over time, set this value to a specific model version.
